The Ministry of Economic Development wants to accelerate the growth of the electric car market
This week, the Ministry of Economic Development will bring to the government a comprehensive plan for the development of environmentally friendly transport in Russia, said Deputy Director of the Department of the Ministry Oleg Pluzhnikov at a round table held by "Vedomosti" at the Moscow Motor Show - 2014.
The plan was drawn up on behalf of the government, one of the main goals is to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.
It is expected that the document will be adopted in late September - early October, says Pluzhnikov, the proposed measures concern electric vehicles and hybrids - a plan for the development of gas-powered vehicles in Russia already exists.
The plan (a copy has "Vedomosti") is designed for 2014-2017.
Criteria for the assessment of electric and hybrid transport should be developed and how to encourage the use and production of environmentally friendly vehicles.
The report to the government, which will describe tax and customs measures to support electric transport, will be prepared by December 2014; the scheme of preferential lending and leasing will appear by April 2015; and proposals for lowering the price of cars, stimulating localization and creating service infrastructure will be developed by October 2015.
In 2014-2015, it is planned to amend the regulations to facilitate the conditions for the construction of charging infrastructure (in parking lots, gas stations, etc.).
In addition, federal officials intend to formulate proposals for regional authorities during 2015 so that they also encourage the use of environmentally friendly transport - in the form of giving it an advantage in traffic and parking, for example; and by February 2016 - and proposals to expand public procurement of such transport.
Finally, by October 2014, the Ministry of Economic Development will add criteria to the list of indicators for evaluating the performance of regional authorities, reflecting the effectiveness of support for the production of environmentally friendly transport, the development of charging infrastructure.
The electric car market in Russia is only forming - in 2013 about 100 electric cars were sold in the whole country.
In early 2014, the import duty on electric cars was zeroed, so sales will be about 500 pieces, predicts the chief executive of Mitsubishi Motors in Russia Andrey Pankov.
But the five-fold growth does not make electric cars any noticeable: in 2013, according to the European Business Association, 2.78 million passenger cars and light commercial vehicles were sold in Russia.
So far, only Mitsubishi Motors imports electric cars to Russia.
Renault is preparing to start importing - the company focuses primarily on corporate customers, says Nicolas Remiz, Renault’s Director of Strategic Planning and Partnerships in Russia.
The majority of other manufacturers of electric vehicles took a wait-and-see attitude towards Russia.
There are developments of electric cars and Russian manufacturers - "", GAZ, "", but the production is meager.
For example, in January - July 2014, according to ASM-holding, AvtoVAZ produced 30 electric vehicles.
Demand is low due to the high cost of electric vehicles, admits the director of "AvtoVAZ" for engineering Sergey Amanov, without state support breakthrough in this segment will not be.
The development of the Russian market of electric cars in addition to the high cost of cars (those electric cars sold in Russia, on average, twice as expensive as analogues with internal combustion engines) restrains the underdevelopment of the charging infrastructure (refueling - units), sighs the General Director of "Autostat" Sergey Tselikov.
Due to the high cost and low cost reduction rates, electric vehicles in the next 3-4 years will remain a niche segment of the Russian market, predicts the editor-in-chief of "Autorev" Mikhail Podorohansky, Tselikov agrees with him.
Automakers, on the other hand, say that some models of electric vehicles are already close to the cost of conventional ones.
The Russian electric car market has good prospects, the main thing is to inspire confidence in consumers that "electromobility" is real; this will, in particular, be facilitated by the emergence of more and more new charging stations, emphasizes the president of the BMW Group in Russia, Wolfgang Schlimme.
Such infrastructure projects are implemented, for example, by the state company Rosseti: several stations have been built in Moscow, about 80 more will appear soon.
Negotiations on the construction of a gas station network are also underway with other regions.
According to Vladimir Sofiin, director of the Rossety Department, the company believes in the electric vehicle market and is ready to build refueling stations throughout the country, but there are also problems: a small number of electric vehicles in the country and the lack of a single standard for charging electric vehicles of different brands.
In addition, Rosseti, as a network company, does not have the right to sell electricity, and the possibility of doing so is being worked out in relation to charging electric vehicles.
Pankov believes that the most effective measure of state support for the formation of the electric car market in Russia is the zeroing of customs duties.
The zero rate will be valid until the end of 2014, the possibility of its extension and expansion of the preferential list is being worked out.
Replacing the transport tax with an environmental one (the idea is discussed and applies to all cars) will also support the market, but not as tangible as customs preferences, Pankov believes.
Transport tax in Russia is small, says Pankov, unlike, for example, from Norway, where the tax reduction led to a sharp increase in sales of electric cars - now they account for 12% of the market.
In Russia, we also need incentive measures for car owners, for example, free parking in the city center (as already done in Moscow), Pankov is sure, or the possibility of moving electric cars on designated lanes, which is not yet available in Russia.
