"Europrotocol" instead of traffic police references
Casco payments can be received without a traffic police certificate - so the Central Bank intends to stimulate the introduction of the "Europrotocol" in Russia.
The Bank of Russia has developed a draft guidelines, according to which from September 1 this year, to receive payments on the helmet, the insured motorist will be able to do without a traffic police certificate.
This, however, is only about those cases when the accident was executed under the "Europrotocol" without the participation of the traffic police.
That is, if only two cars participated in the accident, there are no physically injured persons, the damage does not exceed the established limit and both drivers reached an agreement on the question of who is responsible for the accident.
From August 2, the limit of payments under the "Europrotocol" is 50 thousand rubles, and from October 1, in Moscow, St. Petersburg, as well as in the Moscow and Leningrad regions, it will be raised to 400 thousand rubles.
The bottom line is that often even with minor damage, in a situation where an accident can be issued according to the "Europrotocol", drivers caught in an accident, cause DPS.
After all, if there is a policy casco to get a refund on it without a certificate of traffic police was impossible.
The parameters prescribed in the draft guidelines are designed to eliminate this obstacle to the introduction of the “Europrotocol” in Russia.
According to them, the maximum payment on the casco in connection with an accident, executed without traffic police officers, should not be lower than the limit under the "Europrotocol".
But at the same time it can not be higher than the limit specified in the insurance contract casco.
The idea is certainly useful and theoretically capable of unloading both DPS employees and roads.
